5:
Heh-heh-heh-heh... I feel invincible
with this parasol!
8:
Our goal is to conquer every shop
with sweets that Palpebra has to
offer! Let's go to the crepe shop next,
everyone!
13:
Wait a moment! You said you did
not want to push yourself too hard
today!
17:
I wonder if Lumira's okay. She's not
struggling with the sun anymore, at
least...
20:
She's been looking so happy lately,
and seemed really excited for today,
tooâ€”
24: Feh... Huh? I'm feeling kinda... dizzy...
35: Fehh... Maybe I stayed up too late...
39:
You're like the opposite of a night
owl... A day owl?
46:
I know, I'm sorry. I was just having
fun...
50:
Prika. Maybe now's the time we try
that thing out?
55: Good idea! Let's all be night owls!
59:
Hehe. I've been wanting to go to that
castle since I first heard of it.
63:
In other words! We're gonna have a
sleepover at Prika's castle!
70:
This is delicious! You're such a good
cook, Prika!
73:
I got a little better at it with practice!
I even made this potato salad all by
myself!
78: The tomato juice is delicious, too.
82:
I did not realize this could be a
substitute for the blood of the living.
Is the taste really that similar?
86:
Hmm. Does blood taste kinda like
iron, or something?
91:
Iron?! I read in that vampire's book
that "blood tastes better than
anything in the world"!
96:
...I've heard about dishes that use
animal blood in them. Maybe you
could find one of those and try it out?
101:
Ugh... I'm curious, but I'd rather my
first taste of blood be from my first
follower!
106:
That was a great meal. I've got work,
so I gotta head back now.
111:
Do your best, Yuki! Once you're done,
make sure you get your proper rest,
too!
114:
Thank you. Have a good time,
everybody.
118: She really left. How diligent of her.
122:
It's okay. Hanging out with your
friends is always best when
everyone does it at their own pace.
125:
...But I hope she can until the end
someday!
136:
Whoa... Thanks, Prika! Me and my
friends having a sleepover with
matching beds... It's like a dream!
139:
Oh... So vampires really do sleep in
coffins, huh?
143:
It's to keep the sunlight out, but it's
so dark and scary in there that I'd
sleep on the lid instead!
149:
Okay, everyone! Let's get under the
covers! I've been looking forward to
chatting as we drift off to sleep!
153:
Lumira? I have been wondering
about something...
156:
How is it that someone becomes
your follower when you suck their
blood?
160:
I-I don't really know how to explain
the exact process!
164:
Oh... Shall we try the process on
myself, then? As long as I do not
become your underling!
169:
Why are you and Stella so quick to
agree to being bitten? There are
other people around, you know?! It's
embarrassing!
173:
O-oh? Does that mean, biting
someone is basically... THAT sort of
thing?
178: Feh... It's too difficult to explain...
181:
...I understand it for the most part.
Becoming a follower of mine... It
requires that we "bequeath" or souls
to one another.
185:
Your blood enters my body. Your
blood... becomes mine...
187:
So, like... It's a feeling of, um... Mixing
together... Or...
191:
It sounds a little nastier than I
thought...
195: Is it different from making a friend?
200:
Ah! I was thinking the same thing!
Maybe it's like having a friend or
family member living with you!
204:
Does mixing like that mean... You're
not really yourself anymore?
207: Ah, um! I was just wondering...
211:
I think you've got a point, Nao. I
wasn't myself for a time...
214:
I changed, and was different from
everybody else. I was scared... and
lonely.
218:
...But I'm a part of all of you, now.
Every part of me is...
234:
What a sight. The vampire is the first
to slumber at night...
238:
Ahaha. It does seem fitting for
Lumira though, doesn't it?
243:
Perhaps it's time for us to go to sleep
as well.
254:
Even if we're... not the... same...
We're... a part of each other, now..
